rsymbolic2 is an independent re-implementation in C++. Its default
configuration, search behaviour, and several internal mechanisms are derived
from, and were developed by closely studying, the following projects, both of
which are licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0:

  * PySR
    Copyright 2020 Miles Cranmer
    https://github.com/MilesCranmer/PySR

  * SymbolicRegression.jl
    Copyright Miles Cranmer and the SymbolicRegression.jl contributors
    https://github.com/MilesCranmer/SymbolicRegression.jl

The above copyright notices are reproduced here pursuant to Section 4(c) of the
Apache License, Version 2.0. The default values and the search/mutation
mechanisms in rsymbolic2 are deliberately matched to PySR's documented
defaults; the implementation (a Julia-free C++ core, a self-contained
Levenberg-Marquardt constant optimiser, and OpenMP island parallelism) is the
original work of this project.

rsymbolic2 is NOT affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by PySR,
SymbolicRegression.jl, or their authors.

